# Dashboard (Next.js)

App Router lives **only** under `apps/dashboard/src/app`.

## Critical layout rule

- **Never** create `apps/dashboard/app/`, `apps/dashboard/pages/`, or empty root `components/` / `lib/` stubs.
- Next.js prefers root `app/` over `src/app/`. An empty root `app/` makes every route 404 (`/_not-found`).
- Pages, layouts, and `globals.css` stay in `src/app/**`. Shared UI in `src/components`, hooks in `src/hooks`, clients in `src/lib`.

```text
# ❌ BAD — shadows src/app and breaks routing
apps/dashboard/app/

# ✅ GOOD
apps/dashboard/src/app/page.tsx
apps/dashboard/src/app/billing/page.tsx
```

## Conventions

- Client pages that fetch data: `'use client'` + Polaris components.
- API access only through `src/lib/api.ts` (`apiFetch` + bearer token).
- After routing or config changes, delete `.next` if routes look stale, then restart `pnpm dev`.
- Nav items belong in `src/components/Providers.tsx`.
